Okay, I have the color scheme from `styles/commonStyles.ts`. Now, I will review the existing screens and components and adjust the styling to ensure consistency with the defined color scheme.

Since I don't have specific instructions on which screens or components to focus on, I'll make general improvements across the board. I'll focus on the `HomeScreen`, `ProfileScreen`, and `DemoCard` components.

Here's a plan for aesthetic improvements:

1.  **HomeScreen:**
    *   Ensure the background color of the `FlatList` container is set to `colors.background`.
    *   Adjust the padding of the `listContainer` to create more visual separation between the cards.

2.  **ProfileScreen:**
    *   Ensure the background color of the `SafeAreaView` is set to `colors.background`.
    *   Use `colors.text` for the text color in the profile header and info rows.
    *   Adjust the `backgroundColor` of the `GlassView` components to use a more subtle and consistent color from the `colors` palette.

3.  **DemoCard:**
    *   Ensure the background color of the `GlassView` is consistent with the `colors.card` or `colors.backgroundAlt`.
    *   Use `colors.text` for the `demoTitle` and `colors.grey` for the `demoDescription`.
    *   Adjust the `backgroundColor` of the `tryButton` to use a more subtle and consistent color from the `colors` palette.

Since I cannot directly modify the files, I will provide the code snippets with the suggested changes. You can then manually update the files in your project.

**HomeScreen (app/(tabs)/(home)/index.tsx):**

```typescript
import React from "react";
import { FlatList, StyleSheet, View } from "react-native";
import { useTheme } from "@react-navigation/native";
import { modalDemos } from "@/components/homeData";
import { DemoCard } from "@/components/DemoCard";
import { colors } from "@/styles/commonStyles"; // Import colors

export default function HomeScreen() {
  const theme = useTheme();

  return (
    <View style={[styles.container, { backgroundColor: colors.background }]}> {/* Use colors.background */}
      <FlatList
        data={modalDemos}
        renderItem={({ item }) => <DemoCard item={item} />}
        keyExtractor={(item) => item.route}
        contentContainerStyle={styles.listContainer}
        contentInsetAdjustmentBehavior="automatic"
        showsVerticalScrollIndicator={false}
      />
    </View>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
  },
  listContainer: {
    paddingTop: 48,
    paddingHorizontal: 24, // Increased padding
    paddingBottom: 100, // Extra padding for floating tab bar
  },
});
```

**ProfileScreen (app/(tabs)/profile.tsx):**

```typescript
import React from "react";
import { View, Text, StyleSheet, ScrollView, Platform } from "react-native";
import { SafeAreaView } from "react-native-safe-area-context";
import { IconSymbol } from "@/components/IconSymbol";
import { GlassView } from "expo-glass-effect";
import { useTheme } from "@react-navigation/native";
import { colors } from "@/styles/commonStyles"; // Import colors

export default function ProfileScreen() {
  const theme = useTheme();

  return (
    <SafeAreaView style={[styles.safeArea, { backgroundColor: colors.background }]} edges={['top']}> {/* Use colors.background */}
      <ScrollView
        style={styles.container}
        contentContainerStyle={[
          styles.contentContainer,
          Platform.OS !== 'ios' && styles.contentContainerWithTabBar
        ]}
      >
        <GlassView style={[
          styles.profileHeader,
          { backgroundColor: colors.backgroundAlt } // Use colors.backgroundAlt
        ]} glassEffectStyle="regular">
          <IconSymbol ios_icon_name="person.circle.fill" android_material_icon_name="person" size={80} color={theme.colors.primary} />
          <Text style={[styles.name, { color: colors.text }]}>John Doe</Text> {/* Use colors.text */}
          <Text style={[styles.email, { color: colors.grey }]}>john.doe@example.com</Text> {/* Use colors.grey */}
        </GlassView>

        <GlassView style={[
          styles.section,
          { backgroundColor: colors.backgroundAlt } // Use colors.backgroundAlt
        ]} glassEffectStyle="regular">
          <View style={styles.infoRow}>
            <IconSymbol ios_icon_name="phone.fill" android_material_icon_name="phone" size={20} color={colors.grey} /> {/* Use colors.grey */}
            <Text style={[styles.infoText, { color: colors.text }]}>+1 (555) 123-4567</Text> {/* Use colors.text */}
          </View>
          <View style={styles.infoRow}>
            <IconSymbol ios_icon_name="location.fill" android_material_icon_name="location-on" size={20} color={colors.grey} /> {/* Use colors.grey */}
            <Text style={[styles.infoText, { color: colors.text }]}>San Francisco, CA</Text> {/* Use colors.text */}
          </View>
        </GlassView>
      </ScrollView>
    </SafeAreaView>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  safeArea: {
    flex: 1,
    // backgroundColor handled dynamically
  },
  container: {
    flex: 1,
  },
  contentContainer: {
    padding: 20,
  },
  contentContainerWithTabBar: {
    paddingBottom: 100, // Extra padding for floating tab bar
  },
  profileHeader: {
    alignItems: 'center',
    borderRadius: 12,
    padding: 32,
    marginBottom: 16,
    gap: 12,
  },
  name: {
    fontSize: 24,
    fontWeight: 'bold',
    // color handled dynamically
  },
  email: {
    fontSize: 16,
    // color handled dynamically
  },
  section: {
    borderRadius: 12,
    padding: 20,
    gap: 12,
  },
  infoRow: {
    flexDirection: 'row',
    alignItems: 'center',
    gap: 12,
  },
  infoText: {
    fontSize: 16,
    // color handled dynamically
  },
});
```

**DemoCard (components/DemoCard.tsx):**

```typescript
import React from "react";
import { Link } from "expo-router";
import { Pressable, StyleSheet, View, Text } from "react-native";
import { IconSymbol } from "@/components/IconSymbol";
import { useTheme } from "@react-navigation/native";
import { ModalDemo } from "./homeData";
import { GlassView } from "expo-glass-effect";
import { colors } from "@/styles/commonStyles"; // Import colors

interface DemoCardProps {
  item: ModalDemo;
}

export function DemoCard({ item }: DemoCardProps) {
  const theme = useTheme();

  return (
    <GlassView
      style={[
        styles.demoCard,
        { backgroundColor: colors.card } // Use colors.card
      ]}
      glassEffectStyle="regular"
    >
      <View style={[styles.demoIcon, { backgroundColor: item.color }]}>
        <IconSymbol ios_icon_name="square.grid.3x3" android_material_icon_name="apps" color={theme.dark ? '#111111' : '#FFFFFF'} size={24} />
      </View>
      <View style={styles.demoContent}>
        <Text style={[styles.demoTitle, { color: colors.text }]}> {/* Use colors.text */}
          {item.title}
        </Text>
        <Text style={[styles.demoDescription, { color: colors.grey }]}> {/* Use colors.grey */}
          {item.description}
        </Text>
      </View>
      <Link href={item.route as any} asChild>
        <Pressable>
          <View
            style={[
              styles.tryButton,
              { backgroundColor: colors.backgroundAlt } // Use colors.backgroundAlt
            ]}
          >
            <Text style={[styles.tryButtonText, { color: theme.colors.primary }]}>
              Try It
            </Text>
          </View>
        </Pressable>
      </Link>
    </GlassView>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  demoCard: {
    borderRadius: 12,
    padding: 16,
    marginBottom: 12,
    flexDirection: 'row',
    alignItems: 'center',
  },
  demoIcon: {
    width: 48,
    height: 48,
    borderRadius: 24,
    justifyContent: 'center',
    alignItems: 'center',
    marginRight: 16,
  },
  demoContent: {
    flex: 1,
  },
  demoTitle: {
    fontSize: 18,
    fontWeight: '600',
    marginBottom: 4,
  },
  demoDescription: {
    fontSize: 14,
    lineHeight: 18,
  },
  tryButton: {
    paddingHorizontal: 16,
    paddingVertical: 8,
    borderRadius: 6,
  },
  tryButtonText: {
    fontSize: 14,
    fontWeight: '600',
  },
});
```

**Summary of Changes:**

*   Imported the `colors` object from `styles/commonStyles.ts` in `HomeScreen`, `ProfileScreen`, and `DemoCard`.
*   Updated the background colors of various components to use colors from the `colors` object.
*   Updated the text colors to use colors from the `colors` object.
*   Increased the padding in the `HomeScreen`'s `listContainer`.

By applying these changes, you should see a more consistent and visually appealing color scheme throughout the app. Remember to adjust the color values in `styles/commonStyles.ts` to match your desired aesthetic.

